        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ælvīsyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ælvīsyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>ælvyst</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ælvesun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>ælvist</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>прясть</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>spin</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ælvīsinag</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ælvesujnag</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>шерсть на пряжу</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>wool for spinning</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>læg xyzæj axsta kæsægtæ, ūs ta je ʽlvīsinægtæ ælvysta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>муж ловил неводом рыбу, жена пряла свою пряжу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the husband was netting fish; the wife wa spinnig her yarn</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Puškin._Arhau"
                            /><biblScope>3</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>avd xojy se ʽlxujtæ rajstoj, ælvīsinag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>семь сестер взяли свои веретена, пряжу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>seven sisters took their spindles and yarn</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Niger"/><biblScope>94</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>næ wælinʒæbæl æzinæ æz sundak’æ ælviston</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на нашей крыше я вчера пряла шерсть</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>on our roof I spun wool yesterday</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Перестановка из %i*avlīsyn%i (← %i*abi-raiš-%i), ср. такую же
                    метатезу в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ælvasyn"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7lvynyn"><w>lvynyn</w></ref> и др. Перебой %ir%i || %il%i перед %ii%i также
                    закономерен, ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_līʒyn"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7lǧīvyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lvynyn"><w>lvynyn</w></ref> и др. Как
                    и другие термины ткацкого дела (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wafyn"/>),
                    относится к иранскому слою; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>riwis-, riwes-</w>
                        <gloss><q>прясть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>arw'ī́sna</w>
                        <gloss><q>нить</q></gloss></mentioned> (с такой же метатезой, как в ос.!),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>wrēšәl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>brēsaγ, rēsaγ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>rīštan</w></mentioned>: %ires-%i ‘прясть’ (сюда же относят <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ābrēšum</w>
                        <gloss><q>шелк</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>rēsa</w>
                        <gloss><q>пряжа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>rēš- rišati</w>
                        <gloss><q>рвать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>щипать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_lystæg"/> | %ilistæg%i ‘мелкий’ <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>
                    производит от этого же корня. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wafyn"/>, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_nyvændyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lx0yj"><w>lxuj</w></ref>,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wædært"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 159</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Gauthiot</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSL"
                            /><biblScope>XX 10</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Metathesis from %i*avlīsyn%i (← %i*abi-raiš-%i), cf. the same
                    metathesis in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ælvasyn"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7lvynyn"><w>lvynyn</w></ref> etc. The alternation %ir%i || %il%i before %ii%i is
                    also regular, cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_līʒyn"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7lǧīvyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lvynyn"><w>lvynyn</w></ref> etc. Like
                    other weaving terms (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wafyn"/>), it is Iranian;
                    cf. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>riwis-, riwes-</w>
                        <gloss><q>spin</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>arw'ī́sna</w>
                        <gloss><q>thread</q></gloss></mentioned> (with the same metathesis as in
                    Ossetic!), <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>wrēšәl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>brēsaγ, rēsaγ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>rīštan</w></mentioned>: %ires-%i ‘spin’ (to here also concerns <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ābrēšum</w>
                        <gloss><q>silk</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>rēsa</w>
                        <gloss><q>yarn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>rēš- rišati</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>pinch</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ossetic <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_lystæg"/> | %ilistæg%i ‘small’ <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl> traces
                    back to the same root. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wafyn"/>, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_nyvændyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lx0yj"><w>lxuj</w></ref>,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wædært"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 159</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Gauthiot</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSL"
                            /><biblScope>XX 10</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
